        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 8:01PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 801 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 22 miles northeast of Geraldine to 18 miles
northeast of Winifred to 22 miles south of Zortman. Movement was
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Judith Landing, Iliad, and Fred Robinson Bridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
